# DRY Principles

Prefer one source of truth. Do not copy-paste logic across layers, scopes, or file pairs.

## Rules

1. **One implementation per concern** — Shared behavior lives in one module; callers import it. Do not fork “almost the same” project vs source, API vs frontend, or router vs service copies.
2. **Extract on the second use** — If the same logic appears (or is about to appear) in two places, pull it into a shared util/hook/service before shipping. Do not wait for a third copy.
3. **Compose, don’t clone** — Prefer thin adapters over duplicated stacks (e.g. shared chat stream turn + scope adapters, not two full chat pipelines).
4. **Reuse existing primitives** — Search the codebase for helpers, types, hooks, and UI components before writing new ones. Match naming and location of existing shared modules.
5. **Single config / mapping** — Provider maps, auth token parsing, env lookups, and URL builders have one canonical module. Do not re-parse or re-map in feature files.

## Where shared code lives

| Layer | Prefer |
| --- | --- |
| Backend domain/util | `construction_os/utils/`, `construction_os/domain/` |
| API | Shared helpers in services/routers; avoid near-duplicate routers |
| Frontend API/hooks | `frontend/src/lib/api/`, `frontend/src/lib/hooks/` |
| Frontend UI | `frontend/src/components/ui/` then feature components |

## Do

- Extend an existing shared helper when adding a variant
- Pass scope/config as parameters instead of duplicating functions
- Delete the old copy when consolidating (no “legacy twin” left behind)

## Do not

- Copy a function and rename it for a sibling feature
- Maintain parallel project/source (or similar) stacks that differ only in IDs/endpoints
- Duplicate auth, embedding, provider, or stream-parsing logic in components
- Add a second “temporary” implementation without a plan to merge

## Before finishing

- [ ] Searched for an existing helper/type/hook/component
- [ ] No new near-duplicate of an existing stack
- [ ] Shared logic has one owner module; call sites are thin
- [ ] Removed superseded copies after extraction
